thin this framework, the volume focuses on educational and linguistic policies, language teaching and learning, and the didactics that were associated with them.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aImperialism. 0aMissions. 0aSecond language acquisition. 4aContemporary History. 4aEarly Modern Studies. 4aHistory. 4aInternational Relations. 4aLanguage and Literature. 4aLinguistics. 4aModern History. 4aPolitics and Government. 7aHISTORY / Social History.2bisacsh  aHistory of languages learning.  aHistory of languages teaching.  acolonial linguistics.  amissionary linguistics.1 aAbouelgamal, Tarek, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAlbano, Mariangela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAlbano, Mariangela, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aAliffi, Maria Lucia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAvenne, Cécile Van Den, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCowan, Steven, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aErrington, Joseph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFacchin, Andrea, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJin, Tinghe, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKak, Manar El, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMattarucco, Giada, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPantéloglou, Lélia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPham, Thi Kieu Ly, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPhạm, Thị Kiều Ly, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPoli, Diego, econtributor.4ctb4https: